<%= content_for :javascript do %>
  <script>
    $(document).on('click', '.conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link', function() {
      var href = $(this).attr('href');

      if(!$(href).is(':visible')) {
        $('.conveyancing-service-process-item').slideUp();
        $(href).slideDown();
        $('.conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--active').removeClass('conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--active');
        $(this).addClass('conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--active');
      }

      return false;
    });

    $(document).on('click', '.conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button', function() {
      var href = $(this).attr('href');

      if(!$(href).is(':visible')) {
        $('.conveyancing-service-process').slideUp();
        $(href).slideDown();
        $('.conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button--active').removeClass('conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button--active');
        $(this).addClass('conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button--active');
      }

      return false;
    });
  </script>
<% end %>


<% present @service do |service_presenter| %>

  <div class="conveyancing-content conveyancing-content--combined">
    <nav class="conveyancing-content__section conveyancing-content__section--full">
      <section class="conveyancing-service-cta-block">
        <div class="conveyancing-service-content conveyancing-service-content--centered">
          <div class="conveyancing-service-content__title">
            <h2 style="<%= service_presenter.colour_property_helper('border-color') %>">See what happens in our conveyancing process</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="conveyancing-service-content__content">
            <p>
              Selling your home and buying a new one in London can be stressful. At
              Banner Jones, we are expert conveyancing solicitors and we can take
              away some of that pressure; we have a simplified and refined the
              process that will do just that.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-stages-navigation">
          <%= link_to 'Buying Stages',
                      '#buying-stages',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button
                              conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button--active' %>
          <%= link_to 'Selling Stages',
                      '#selling-stages',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-stages-navigation__button' %>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="conveyancing-service-process conveyancing-service-process--selling" id="selling-stages">
         <h3 class="conveyancing-service-process__title">
          The <strong>3 Selling Stages</strong> to our Conveyancing process
        </h3>

        <nav class="conveyancing-service-process-navigation">
          <%= link_to 'Drafting a contract',
                      '#stage-1',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--first
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--active' %>
          <%= link_to 'Exchange of contracts',
                      '#stage-2',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--second' %>
          <%= link_to 'Completion',
                      '#stage-3',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--third' %>
        </nav>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-1">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              If you're happy to accept the quote, we will send the relevant paperwork to begin the conveyancing process.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Contact your mortgage lender. Ask for a Final Redemption Statement. This document will tell us how much money is left outstanding on your mortgage.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We will contact the Land Registry and obtain the relevant information to make a draft version of your contract.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Once the contract is drafted, and you're happy with the terms and conditions, the buyer's solicitor will receive a copy.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              The buyer's solicitor will read the contract and begin conducting mandatory local searches on the property. This part of the process may take some time.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              The buyer's solicitor may ask some questions regarding the contract if so these queries will need addressing.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Once both parties are happy with the terms and conditions, a completion date can be arranged.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-2">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              When the contracts begin the exchange, the transaction is now officially legally binding.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              The deposit from the buyer is transferred to us from the buyer's solicitor.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We will request that you provide us with the Final Redemption Statement from your mortgage lender.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-3">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              By or on the agreed moving date, the buyer's solicitor will transfer the remaining balance of the property's asking price over to us.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Once the property has been paid in full, the estate agent will release the keys over to the new owner.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We will use the funds from the buyer to pay off your existing mortgage. Any balance outstanding from selling the property will be paid and you will receive any remaining balance.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Congratulations.  You have sold your home.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="conveyancing-service-process conveyancing-service-process--buying" id="buying-stages">
        <h3 class="conveyancing-service-process__title">
          The <strong>3 Buying Stages</strong> to our Conveyancing process
        </h3>

        <nav class="conveyancing-service-process-navigation">
          <%= link_to 'Search and paperwork',
                      '#stage-1',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--first
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--active' %>
          <%= link_to 'Exchange of contracts',
                      '#stage-2',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--second' %>
          <%= link_to 'Completion',
                      '#stage-3',
                      class: 'conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link
                              conveyancing-service-process-navigation__link--third' %>
        </nav>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-1">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Agree quote then sign and return your Client care letter,
              instructing us to work on your behalf
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We contact the sellersâ€™ solicitor for the property information,
              deeds and contract
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We conduct local authority searches (can take 2 weeks to come back)
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We receive your mortgage offer (where applicable)
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We review the search results and property info and raise any queries
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              You arrange the 10% deposit (where applicable)
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              We request contract signing
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-2">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Agree on a completion date, so that both parties know when the ownership of the property will be exchanged.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Once you are happy with the agreement, you will need to pay the deposit and sign the contract. After signing the after, the transaction becomes legally binding.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Your solicitor will request money from your mortgage lender.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="conveyancing-service-process-item" id="stage-3">
          <ul class="conveyancing-service-process-point">
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              The financial transaction and ownership of the property must be processed on or by the completion date. Once done, the buyer will be given the keys to their new property.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Congratulations. You officially own the property.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              If any Stamp Duty Land Tax is owed on the property, your solicitor will arrange this transaction.
            </li>
            <li class="conveyancing-service-process-point__item">
              Your solicitor will inform the Land Registry that the ownership of the property has changed.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>
